        "posted_at": "2026-01-28 17:03:05",
        "timestamp_ms": 1769616185429,
        "text": "When VCs and analysts get together they talk about context graphs and trillion-dollar opportunities. When data practitioners get together they ask - -\n\n1. Are you also thinking about building a context graph? \n2. What does it let you do that you weren't able to do before? \n3. Are agents actually doing better because of that? How do you even attribute? What about evals?\n4. Also, where did you even start from? Do you start with blindly integrating systems or throw the kitchen sink of policies on the agent? \n5. What does even a good context graph look like? How do you even define \"good\"? \n\nAnd a million other questions. We have gone through these questions because a bunch of our apps are now in production. and that's what Vivek Khandelwal and Dilip Ittyera will cover in our first linkedin live of this year.  Join us. 30th Jan Friday. 5PM IST.",
        "author": {
