      {
        "urn": "urn:li:activity:7446942960081948672",
        "url": "https://www.linkedin.com/posts/dylanitzikowitz_designers-can-now-ship-without-an-engineer-activity-7446942960081948672-Gwf-?utm_source=social_share_send&utm_medium=member_desktop_web&rcm=ACoAAGbYilkBsT-7xuT6Ux9P0MMOzZMgTeRaYDw",
        "post_type": "repost",
        "posted_at": "2026-04-06 17:37:54",
        "timestamp_ms": 1775489874511,
        "text": "Designers can now ship without an engineer. Small teams can build what once took entire departments. What does this shift mean for the future of work in tech?\n\nJoin us at South Park Commons NYC for a conversation with:\n\nThomas Paul Mann, CEO & Co-founder Raycast\nTom Moor, Head of Engineering @ Linear \nMichael Cohen, API Agents Anthropic\n\nWe’ll dig into how AI-native tooling is reshaping how products get built and who builds them.",
