      {
        "urn": "urn:li:ugcPost:7445514487098515456",
        "url": "https://www.linkedin.com/posts/southparkcommons_how-often-are-you-raging-at-your-ai-spc-activity-7445515129515061248-oxYA?utm_source=social_share_send&utm_medium=member_desktop_web&rcm=ACoAAGbYilkBsT-7xuT6Ux9P0MMOzZMgTeRaYDw",
        "post_type": "regular",
        "posted_at": "2026-04-02 18:58:57",
        "timestamp_ms": 1775149137858,
        "text": "How often are you raging at your AI? \n\nSPC members Parker Lowe, Asher Jiang, and Zack M.'s debate over whether we should say “please” and “thank you” to chatbots opens into broader questions about how conversational AI is fundamentally altering human language, our capacity for critical thinking, and our relationship to each other.",
