      {
        "urn": "urn:li:ugcPost:7445108421449637888",
        "url": "https://www.linkedin.com/posts/dylanitzikowitz_nyc-showed-up-for-our-building-at-the-frontier-ugcPost-7445108421449637888-F3rW?utm_source=social_share_send&utm_medium=member_desktop_web&rcm=ACoAAGbYilkBsT-7xuT6Ux9P0MMOzZMgTeRaYDw",
        "post_type": "repost",
        "posted_at": "2026-04-01 16:05:05",
        "timestamp_ms": 1775052305699,
        "text": "NYC showed up for our Building at the Frontier panel at South Park Commons yesterday. We were packed wall-to-wall with researchers, founders, and operators working on the hardest problems.\n\nNew York is increasingly becoming a real hub for frontier innovation across AI, robotics, and the physical world.\n\nHuge thank you to our speakers building:\n\n- Joseph F. Krause (Radical AI) on how AI is unlocking new material discovery\n-Rob Cochran (Fauna Robotics, acquired by Amazon) on the future of consumer robotics\n-Pim de Witte (General Intuition) on using gaming to train best-in-class world models\n\nAnd thanks to our friend Eric Newcomer for the sharp moderation.\n\nThe frontier is being built here in NYC and we'd love to support more of it!\n\nFull video of the discussion to come soon 👀",
        "author": {
          "name": "Dylan Itzikowitz",
          "username": null,
